folder: Elliott Place N. & Park Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
original_title: Brooklyn: Elliott Place N. - Park Avenue
text:
North Elliott Place, south from Park Avenue. Showin is part of the vast cleared area for Fort Greene Houses, looking northwestward. View 3 shows the New Cumberland Hospital at Auburn Place.
P. L. Sperr  September 6, 1929
NO REPRODUCTIONS  Views 1-8

folder: Elliott Place N. & Park Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
original_title: Brooklyn: Elliott Place N. - Park Avenue
text:
North Elliott Place, south from Park Avenue. The row of low dwellings and on the east side of the street, across which can be seen the New Cumberland Hospital at Auburn Place. The wire fence on the right marks the playground of Public School 67. The cleared area in the foreground, at Park Avenue is where Fort Greene Houses will be erected.

View 2 is on North Elliott Place, looking north toward Park Avenue. View 3 is on the north side of Park Avenue.
P. L. Sperr  April 11, 1941
NO REPRODUCTIONS  Views 1,2,3
